tourBios.carHigh:
2011: Finished sixth on the OneAsia Order of Merit, with $138,741 in earnings. 

2010: In second of two Web.com Tour starts, fired a final-round, 6-under 66 to finish T10 at the Moonah Classic...Finished third on the OneAsia Tour Order of Merit, earning a little more than $247,000. Jumped nearly 300 spots in the Official World Golf Ranking following his OneAsia Tour victory at the Indonesian Open in July.
tourBios.personal: Says winning tournaments is his biggest thrill in golf...Favorite course to play is Gulf Harbour in New Zealand and would like to play Augusta National. Favorite TV show is "Family Guy" and "The Blind Side" is his favorite movie. The Harry Potter series are his favorite books. Chocolate is his favorite food. Favorite athlete to watch is Tiger Woods. The New Zealand rugby team All Blacks is his favorite team. Las Vegas is his favorite city to visit, and the Golf Coast of Australia and Hawaii are his favorite vacation spots...Would include Woods and Sean Connery in his dream foursome...Has one brother and one sister.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T10th in 2010 at the Moonah Classic.
